---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import QuickAnswer from '../components/QuickAnswer.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import PersonSchema from '../components/schema/PersonSchema.astro';
import AboutPageSchema from '../components/schema/AboutPageSchema.astro';
import BreadcrumbSchema from '../components/schema/BreadcrumbSchema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const quickAnswer =
  'Perfume Picks is an iOS app for fragrance collectors, built and run by ' +
  'one independent developer. It catalogs your wardrobe, logs every wear, ' +
  'and recommends bottles you already own. It is not a retailer, not a ' +
  'scraper of competitor sites, and not an ad platform. The app makes ' +
  'money from an optional Pro subscription and retailer affiliate links.';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Perfume Picks — who runs it, what it is, what it isn't, and how it makes money."
  path="/about"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <AboutPageSchema />
    <PersonSchema />
    <BreadcrumbSchema crumbs={[{ name: 'About', url: `${SITE.url}/about` }]} />
  </Fragment>

  <p class="brand">{SITE.name}</p>
  <h1>About Perfume Picks</h1>
  <p class="effective">A collector's wardrobe and wear log — built and run by one person.</p>

  <QuickAnswer text={quickAnswer} />

  <h2>Who runs Perfume Picks?</h2>
  <p>
    Perfume Picks is built and operated by <strong>{SITE.founder.name}</strong>,
    an independent developer and longtime fragrance collector. There is no
    investor, no parent company, and no advertising network behind the app.
    Decisions about features, privacy, and direction are made by one person,
    and that person answers the email at
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What is Perfume Picks?</h2>
  <p>
    Perfume Picks is an iOS app for fragrance collectors. It does four things
    well: catalog your wardrobe with status, remaining mL, and purchase price;
    log every wear with weather and occasion captured automatically; build a
    taste profile from your real collection and your swipe feedback; and
    suggest something to wear tonight from bottles you already own. A yearly
    Perfume Wrapped recap closes the loop with the stats only your own data
    can produce.
  </p>

  <h2>What Perfume Picks is not</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>It is <strong>not a retailer</strong>. The app does not sell fragrance. When you want to buy, we link out to retailers and may earn a small commission.</li>
    <li>It is <strong>not a scraper</strong> of other fragrance sites. Our catalog comes from commercial fragrance-data providers and manual curation.</li>
    <li>It is <strong>not a marketplace</strong>. There are no buy/sell flows, no auctions, no decant exchange.</li>
    <li>It does <strong>not show ads</strong>. There are no ads anywhere in the app or on this site.</li>
    <li>It does <strong>not sell or share your data</strong> for cross-user ad targeting. Your wardrobe and wear log are private by default. See the <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for the full breakdown.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How Perfume Picks makes money</h2>
  <p>
    Two revenue streams, both transparent. First, an optional <strong>Pro
    subscription</strong> unlocks the full taste quiz, unlimited Train My Nose
    swipes, the taste profile screen, advanced analytics, and Perfume Wrapped.
    Subscriptions are managed through Apple via RevenueCat, so payment
    information never touches our servers.
  </p>
  <p>
    Second, fragrance detail pages may include <strong>&ldquo;Buy from&rdquo;</strong>
    links to retailers such as FragranceX, Sephora, and Amazon Luxury Beauty.
    When you use one of those links and purchase, we may earn a small commission
    at no cost to you. This is disclosed on the page where the link appears and
    in the <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>. The price you pay is the same.
  </p>

  <h2>Why an independent developer built this</h2>
  <p>
    The fragrance internet has not been served well. The most-cited reference
    sites are dated, ad-heavy, and treat the collector like a row in a database.
    Newer entrants are feature-thin and focused on discovery for shoppers, not
    on collectors who already own dozens of bottles and want to actually wear
    them. Perfume Picks is built for the collector who needs a wardrobe, a
    wear log, and a private taste profile in one place &mdash; without ads,
    without scraping, and without being pushed toward the next purchase.
  </p>

  <h2>Editorial standards</h2>
  <p>
    Articles published on this site are written by {SITE.founder.name} based
    on first-hand experience as a collector and on cited primary sources
    (manufacturer notes, perfumer interviews, IFRA documentation, and other
    public sources). When a fact comes from somewhere other than direct
    experience, it is linked. When something is an opinion, it is labeled.
  </p>
  <p>
    Articles are dated, and the date is updated only when the content
    actually changes &mdash; not just to make the page look fresh.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Press, partnership, or product feedback:
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>.
    There is no DM channel &mdash; email is the canonical contact.
  </p>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
